It is believed that Bonnie and Clyde owned one such copy of the M1921A type, but there is no exhaustive evidence of this, and the same copy was sold on January 21, 2012 in Kansas for 130 thousand US dollars [77]. The main principle is a semi-free shutter according to the Blish system ( English) Russian, created in 1915 by US Navy officer John Blish. It is a part of a complex shape in two parts. The front part is a cylindrical shape with a diameter slightly larger than the cartridge, which consists of an extractor and a striker. with an extremely flat ramp.